        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Thank you for chiming in, @wookayin, that's helpful to know.\r\n\r\nI guess out of excitement about 0.10.0, eagerness to install and use it and the frustration that it appeared so broken for me I hastily created this issue. I should've been more level headed and analysed the issue more thoroughly and narrowed it down before opening an issue.\r\nApplying some common sense would've been helpful too, _if_ the latest official neovim release or neovim nixpkgs was \"so broken\" others would've very likely caught it already.\r\n\r\nThe good news: the issue is resolved; the bad news: I'm not sure why… Running `nix run nixpkgs#neovim -- --clean +help` is enough proof for me that the issue must've been with some oddity in my setup even though \"nothing changed\" apart from installing new nixpkgs generations…",
