        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> The good news: the issue is resolved; the bad news: I'm not sure why… Running `nix run nixpkgs#neovim -- --clean +help` is enough proof for me that the issue must've been with some oddity in my setup even thought \"nothing changed\" apart from installing new nixpkgs generations…\r\n\r\n\"nothing changed\" that's not true, I made a PR on nixpkgs to update the bundled tree-sitter parsers for neovim 0.10\r\nhttps://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/pull/312312\r\nAnd it recently hit the unstable branch, hence you're getting the new parsers which are compatible with nvim' queries 🙃",
